moveMenuNode

public static void moveMenuNode(org.w3c.dom.Node menuDocument,
                                java.lang.String nodeId,
                                java.lang.String parentId,
                                java.lang.String nextId,
                                java.lang.String prevId)
Internal - ApplCore Use Only. This method is used to move a menu node within the menutree xml. The parentId, nextId, and prevId are mutually exclusive and will treated in the following order. If parentId is set the menu node will be appended to the node representing the parentId eg. parentNode.appendChild. If nextId is set the menu node will be inserted directly before the nextId node in the tree. If prevId is set the menu node will be inserted directly after the prevId node in the tree. If prevId node does not exist the node will be appended as a child of the parent of the node pointed to by id.

Parameters:
menuDocument - the DOM document for the menu xml.
nodeId - the id of the node to move
parentId - the node to appendChild to.
nextId - the node will insert before.
prevId - the node will insert after.
